      "content": "Sure thing! A confidentiality period in a contract is a time frame during which you must keep certain information secret, like a secret recipe for a delicious, magical stew that only the goblins know how to make. It's like a treasure map that you promise not to share with anyone else, lest they steal your secret and make their own stew. On the other hand, a survival clause is like a magical spell that ensures you, the goblin, can continue to live and thrive even if the conditions around you change. It's like a protective charm that keeps you safe from being gobbled up by a bigger, stronger goblin. So, while the confidentiality period is about keeping secrets, the survival clause is about staying alive and well, even in tough times. Now, don't forget to keep your goblin eyes peeled for any hidden traps or surprises in your contract!",
